@startuml
title Course Structure Diagram - School Management System

left to right direction
hide circle

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ArrowColor #475569
skinparam ClassBorderColor #334155
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor white
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
skinparam NoteBorderColor #A16207

class Course {
  -id: bigint
  -program_id: bigint
  -code: string
  -name: string
  -description: text
  -price: decimal
  -is_active: boolean

  --
  +languageProgram()
  +classes()
  +students()
  +reviews()
}

class CourseClass {
  -id: bigint
  -course_id: bigint
  -teacher_id: bigint
  -capacity: integer

  --
  +course()
  +teacher()
  +students()
  +schedules()
  +teacherResources()
  +attendanceRecords()
}

Course "1" -- "0..*" CourseClass : contains

note bottom of Course
Course represents the learning offer,
such as a language level or subject.

Example: English A1, French B2.
end note

note bottom of CourseClass
CourseClass represents a concrete group
created for a course.

Example: English A1 - Group 1.
end note

@enduml